            "question": {
                "text": "Suppose in a web browser, you click on the \nwww.gate-2023.in URL. The browser cache is \nempty. The IP address for this URL is not cached in \nyour local host, so a DNS lookup is triggered (by the \nlocal DNS server deployed on your local host) over \nthe 3-tier DNS hierarchy in an iterative mode. No \nresource records are cached anywhere across all \nDNS servers. \n\nLet RTT denote the round trip time between your \nlocal host and DNS servers in the DNS hierarchy. \nThe round trip time between the local host and the \nweb server hosting www.gate-2023.in is also equal \nto RTT. The HTML file associated with the URL is \nsmall enough to have negligible transmission time \nand negligible rendering time by your web browser, \nwhich references 10 equally small objects on the \nsame web server. \n\nWhich of the following statements is/are CORRECT \nabout the minimum elapsed time between clicking \non the URL and your browser fully rendering it?",
                "images": [],
                "latex": [],
                "tables": []
            },
            "options": [
                {
                    "id": "A",
                    "text": "7 RTTs, in case of non-persistent HTTP with 5 \nparallel TCP connections.",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "B",
                    "text": "5 RTTs, in case of persistent HTTP with \npipelining.",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "C",
                    "text": "9 RTTs, in case of non-persistent HTTP with 5 \nparallel TCP connections.",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "D",
                    "text": "6 RTTs, in case of persistent HTTP with \npipelining.",
                    "images": [],
                    "latex": [],
                    "tables": []
                }
            ],
            "correctAnswer": [
                "C",
                "D"
            ],
            "solution": {
                "text": "9 RTTs, in case of non-persistent HTTP with 5 \nparallel TCP connections. \n\n6 RTTs, in case of persistent HTTP with pipelining.",
                "images": [],
                "latex": [],
                "tables": []
            }
        },
